# Everything under data/ is operator-local and must never enter git.
#
# That includes:
#   - secrets (bootstrap-passwords.json, .devicecontrol-secret-key)
#   - inventories (real host names, IPs, bootstrap_user values — site config)
#   - operational output (run_logs/, screenshots/, stats/, device_events/,
#     display_events/)
#   - any future subdirectory under data/
#
# Blanket-ignore rather than allowlist: a tracked inventory file leaks the
# tailnet topology, a tracked run log leaks host output, and a tracked
# password file leaks actual credentials. We want zero chance of any of
# those ending up in `git add`.
#
# The Flask app self-seeds an empty `[ungrouped]` inventory on first
# request (see app/__init__.py env_dir), so a fresh clone works without
# any tracked seed file.
/data/

# Flask / process bookkeeping
.devicecontrol-*.pid
